eNCA's Siphokazi Malinga spoke to the former Usuthu defender about the Premiership's KZN factor. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - The last time a KwaZulu-Natal side won the league was back in the 1996/1997 season. Back then, Manning Rangers walked away with the Premiership title. This past season, AmaZulu's exploits and Golden Arrows' promising campaign impressed Gavin Lane. READ: McCarthy's fine season at AmaZulu Lane is excited by the potential of current KZN clubs and feels the DSTV Premiership title is not out of reach for them. eNCA's Siphokazi Malinga spoke to the former Usuthu defender about the Premiership's KZN factor. Watch the full interview in the video above.